NNAAMMEE
	 mrcv - view mrc data files in batch mode.

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
	 mrcv [batch file] [-v]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN

	when mrcv is called with a batch filename instead of an image
	file name it enters batch mode.

	When in batch mode:

	The default window is an ntsc window, the -n option is ignored, 
	use the -f option for a full sized window.

	The -r option has no effect.

	The -s option is used to scale coordinates to either fit a 
	display	device or to compensate for the differece in ntsc 
	and full sized windows.

	Debuging information will be written to standard out unless the
	-h option is used.


	Batch file format:

	The batch file MUST begin with the line
	mrcv 1.0
	This way mrcv knows that the file is an mrcv batch file.

	Empty lines and lines that begin with # are ignored.

	All command line begin with a %, then a space, then one of the
	commands and then possibly a command option.

