COMMAND DESCRIPTION
	

	% load [filename]
		Reads in the filename, where filename is the path name
		of a mrc data file.	

	% loadx [filename] [section] [blacklevel] [whitelevel]
	% loady [filename] [section] [blacklevel] [whitelevel]
	% loadz [filename] [section] [blacklevel] [whitelevel]
		Load an x,y or z slice, and adjust contrast.

	% swap
		Swithes between two possible mrc image data.
	
	% blacklevel [# (0-255)]
		Sets the level where the black end of the colormap
		ramp starts.

	% whitelevel [# (0-255)]
		Sets the level where the white end of the colormap
		ramp ends.

	% backlevel [# (0-255)]
		Sets the gray-level for the background color.

	% titlecolor [# red (0-255)] [# green (0-255)] [# blue (0-255)]

	% setmon [NTSC |  HZ60 |  HZ72]
		Sets the graphics display to video, 60 Hz or 72 Hz.

	% font [fontname] [# point size]
		Fontname is the name of one of the fonts listed below.
		Pointsize is an integer giving a point size.

